# Top 10 countries with most content
plt.figure(figsize=(20, 12))
countries = clean_df['country'].str.split(',').explode()
countries = countries[countries != 'Unavailble']
countries = countries.str.strip().value_counts()

top_10_countries = countries.head(10)
sns.barplot(x=top_10_countries.index, y=top_10_countries.values, palette='viridis')
plt.title('Top 10 Countries by Number of Contents on Disney+')
plt.xlabel('Country')
plt.ylabel('Number of Contents')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.show()

#Top 10 directors

# Extracting directors and excluding 'Unavailable'
directors = clean_df['director'].astype(str).str.split(',').explode().str.strip()
directors = directors[directors != 'Unavailable']

# Count occurrences of each director
director_counts = directors.value_counts()

# Select top 10 directors
top_10_directors = director_counts.head(10)

# Plotting
plt.figure(figsize=(20, 12))
sns.barplot(x=top_10_directors.values, y=top_10_directors.index, palette='viridis')
plt.title('Top 10 Directors with the Most Contents')
plt.xlabel('Number of Contents')
plt.ylabel('Director')
plt.show()
In [17]:
# Top 10 TV Shows with the most seasons

# Filter out rows where type is 'TV Show'
tv_shows = clean_df[clean_df['type'] == 'TV Show']

# Extract the number of seasons from the 'duration' column
tv_shows['num_seasons'] = tv_shows['duration'].str.extract('(\d+)').astype(int)

# Sort TV shows by the number of seasons in descending order
tv_shows_sorted = tv_shows.sort_values(by='num_seasons', ascending=False)

# Select top 10 TV shows with the most seasons
top_10_tv_shows = tv_shows_sorted.head(10)

# Plotting
plt.figure(figsize=(20, 12))
sns.barplot(x='num_seasons', y='title', data=top_10_tv_shows, palette='viridis')
plt.title('Top 10 TV Shows with the Most Seasons')
plt.xlabel('Number of Seasons')
plt.ylabel('TV Show')
plt.show()

# Filter out rows where type is 'TV Show'
tv_season = clean_df[clean_df['type'] == 'TV Show']

# Extract the number of seasons from the 'duration' column
tv_season['num_seasons'] = tv_season['duration'].str.extract('(\d+)').astype(int)

# Count the number of TV shows for each number of seasons

plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.show()
